## Bulkhead Pattern: Isolating Downstream Failures

### Root cause: shared pool starvation
Recommendations holds connections for 800ms. The shared pool (e.g., 20 connections) fills up with waiting recommendation calls. Inventory calls queue behind them and time out even though inventory is healthy.

### Fix: Thread-pool bulkhead per downstream
```java
// Separate named thread pools
ThreadPoolBulkheadConfig inventoryPool = ThreadPoolBulkheadConfig.custom()
    .maxThreadPoolSize(10)
    .coreThreadPoolSize(5)
    .queueCapacity(20)
    .keepAliveDuration(Duration.ofMillis(20))
    .build();

ThreadPoolBulkheadConfig recommendationsPool = ThreadPoolBulkheadConfig.custom()
    .maxThreadPoolSize(5)          // intentionally smaller
    .coreThreadPoolSize(2)
    .queueCapacity(5)
    .keepAliveDuration(Duration.ofMillis(20))
    .build();

ThreadPoolBulkhead inventoryBulkhead =
    ThreadPoolBulkhead.of("inventory", inventoryPool);
ThreadPoolBulkhead recommendationsBulkhead =
    ThreadPoolBulkhead.of("recommendations", recommendationsPool);
```

### Separate HTTP clients with per-client timeouts
```java
@Bean
public InventoryClient inventoryClient() {
    return WebClient.builder()
        .baseUrl(inventoryUrl)
        .clientConnector(new ReactorClientHttpConnector(
            HttpClient.create().responseTimeout(Duration.ofMillis(200))
        ))
        .build();
}

@Bean
public RecommendationsClient recommendationsClient() {
    return WebClient.builder()
        .baseUrl(recommendationsUrl)
        .clientConnector(new ReactorClientHttpConnector(
            HttpClient.create().responseTimeout(Duration.ofSeconds(1))
        ))
        .build();
}
```

### Degraded-mode fallback for slow service
```java
public CompletableFuture<List<String>> getRecommendations(String userId) {
    return Try.ofSupplier(
        ThreadPoolBulkhead.decorateSupplier(recommendationsBulkhead,
            () -> recommendationsClient.fetch(userId))
    ).recover(BulkheadFullException.class, ex ->
        cachedRecommendations.getOrDefault(userId, Collections.emptyList())
    ).get();
}
```
When the recommendations bulkhead is full, return cached/default recommendations rather than failing the entire request.

