## Structured Logging: From Grep to Query

### Replace unstructured strings with JSON
```xml
<!-- logback-spring.xml -->
<appender name="JSON" class="ch.qos.logback.core.ConsoleAppender">
  <encoder class="net.logstash.logback.encoder.LogstashEncoder">
    <customFields>{"service":"payment-service","env":"prod"}</customFields>
  </encoder>
</appender>
```

Now every log line is machine-parseable:
```json
{
  "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:23:45.123Z",
  "level": "ERROR",
  "service": "payment-service",
  "traceId": "abc123def456",
  "spanId": "789xyz",
  "userId": "usr-9871",
  "paymentId": "pay-4421",
  "amount": 99.99,
  "currency": "USD",
  "errorCode": "INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS",
  "message": "Payment processing failed"
}
```

### Propagate trace ID via MDC
```java
@Component
public class TraceIdFilter implements Filter {
    @Override
    public void doFilter(ServletRequest req, ServletResponse res, FilterChain chain) {
        String traceId = Optional
            .ofNullable(((HttpServletRequest) req).getHeader("X-Trace-Id"))
            .orElse(UUID.randomUUID().toString());

        MDC.put("traceId", traceId);
        MDC.put("requestPath", ((HttpServletRequest) req).getRequestURI());
        try {
            ((HttpServletResponse) res).addHeader("X-Trace-Id", traceId);
            chain.doFilter(req, res);
        } finally {
            MDC.clear(); // critical: prevents MDC leaks in thread pools
        }
    }
}
```

### Propagate to downstream HTTP calls
```java
@Bean
public RestTemplate restTemplate() {
    RestTemplate rt = new RestTemplate();
    rt.getInterceptors().add((request, body, execution) -> {
        request.getHeaders().add("X-Trace-Id", MDC.get("traceId"));
        return execution.execute(request, body);
    });
    return rt;
}
```

### Enrich with business context
```java
@Service
public class PaymentService {
    public PaymentResult process(PaymentRequest req) {
        MDC.put("userId", req.getUserId());
        MDC.put("paymentId", req.getPaymentId());
        MDC.put("amount", String.valueOf(req.getAmount()));
        try {
            return doProcess(req);
        } finally {
            MDC.remove("userId");
            MDC.remove("paymentId");
            MDC.remove("amount");
        }
    }
}
```

### Result: cross-service trace in one query
```
traceId:"abc123def456" | fields timestamp, service, level, message
```
One query surfaces the full request journey across all 12 services ordered by timestamp.

## Detecting Silent Business Failures

### How 72 hours of silence happened
Typical root causes:
1. Catch block swallowed exception and returned `200 {"status": "ok"}` without persisting
2. A feature flag silently routed to a no-op code path
3. Database write succeeded but message publish failed — order created but never fulfilled
4. Async step (email, inventory reservation) failed with no observable effect on the HTTP response

### Fix 1: Business metric counters
```java
@Service
public class OrderService {
    private final Counter ordersAttempted;
    private final Counter ordersCreated;
    private final Counter ordersFailed;

    public OrderService(MeterRegistry registry) {
        this.ordersAttempted = registry.counter("orders.attempted");
        this.ordersCreated   = registry.counter("orders.created");
        this.ordersFailed    = registry.counter("orders.failed");
    }

    public OrderResult createOrder(OrderRequest req) {
        ordersAttempted.increment();
        try {
            Order order = orderRepository.save(toOrder(req));
            eventPublisher.publish(new OrderCreatedEvent(order));
            ordersCreated.increment();
            return OrderResult.success(order.getId());
        } catch (Exception e) {
            ordersFailed.increment(); // never swallow silently
            log.error("Order creation failed", e);
            throw e;
        }
    }
}
```

### Fix 2: Success rate alert (not just error rate)
```yaml
# Prometheus alerting rule
- alert: OrderSuccessRateLow
  expr: |
    rate(orders_created_total[5m])
    / rate(orders_attempted_total[5m]) < 0.98
  for: 2m
  labels:
    severity: critical
  annotations:
    summary: "Order success rate below 98% for 2 minutes"
```
This fires even when HTTP 200 is returned — it measures business outcomes.

### Fix 3: Reconciliation probe
```java
@Scheduled(fixedDelay = 300_000) // every 5 minutes
public void reconcileOrders() {
    Instant fiveMinutesAgo = Instant.now().minus(5, ChronoUnit.MINUTES);
    long attempted = orderAttemptLog.countSince(fiveMinutesAgo);
    long persisted  = orderRepository.countCreatedSince(fiveMinutesAgo);
    double successRate = attempted > 0 ? (double) persisted / attempted : 1.0;
    if (successRate < 0.98) {
        alertingService.fire("OrderDropRate",
            String.format("%.1f%% of orders persisted in last 5m", successRate * 100));
    }
}
```

### Fix 4: Idempotency audit trail
Log a structured event with a unique requestId at the very start (before any processing) and at the very end. A gap in the audit trail is detectable even without errors.

