## UX Patterns for Hiding Eventual Consistency

### The three approaches

#### 1. Optimistic UI (client-side, no backend change)
Show the user's action immediately, reconcile later:
```javascript
// React example
const [comments, setComments] = useState(serverComments);

const handlePostComment = async (text) => {
    const optimistic = { id: 'temp-' + Date.now(), text, author: currentUser, pending: true };
    setComments(prev => [...prev, optimistic]);  // show immediately

    try {
        const real = await api.postComment(text);
        setComments(prev => prev.map(c =>
            c.id === optimistic.id ? { ...real, pending: false } : c
        ));
    } catch (err) {
        setComments(prev => prev.filter(c => c.id !== optimistic.id)); // rollback
        showError('Failed to post comment');
    }
};
```

#### 2. Read-your-writes: route user's reads to primary
```java
@Component
public class ReadRoutingInterceptor implements HandlerInterceptor {
    private final RedisTemplate<String, String> redis;

    @Override
    public boolean preHandle(HttpServletRequest request, ...) {
        String userId = getCurrentUserId(request);
        if (userId != null) {
            // Check if user recently wrote (within 5s)
            String flag = redis.opsForValue().get("recent-write:" + userId);
            if (flag != null) {
                // Tag request to use primary DB
                request.setAttribute("USE_PRIMARY", true);
            }
        }
        return true;
    }
}

// After a write:
@PostMapping("/comments")
public ResponseEntity<Comment> postComment(...) {
    commentRepository.save(comment);
    // Mark this user as having recently written
    redis.opsForValue().set("recent-write:" + userId, "1", Duration.ofSeconds(10));
    return ResponseEntity.status(201).body(comment);
}
```

#### 3. Serve the write response directly in the read
Return the written object in the POST response and merge it on the client — don't re-fetch after write:
```
POST /comments → 201 { id: "abc", text: "...", createdAt: "..." }
// Client appends this directly to UI state without refetching
```

### Consistency model taxonomy
| Model | User experience | Cost |
|---|---|---|
| Strong | Always current | High latency |
| Read-your-writes | User sees own writes | Medium |
| Monotonic read | No going back in time | Low |
| Eventual | May see stale briefly | Lowest |

