## Poison Pill: Unblocking a Kafka Partition

### Why the partition stops
Kafka consumers process messages in offset order within a partition. When message at offset 14523 throws `SerializationException`, the consumer cannot advance past it without committing the offset. Default behavior: retry indefinitely — the partition is stuck.

### Immediate fix: Dead Letter Topic handler
```java
@Configuration
public class KafkaConsumerConfig {
    @Bean
    public DefaultErrorHandler errorHandler(
            KafkaTemplate<String, byte[]> kafkaTemplate) {

        // Send unprocessable messages to dead-letter topic
        DeadLetterPublishingRecoverer recoverer =
            new DeadLetterPublishingRecoverer(kafkaTemplate,
                (record, ex) -> new TopicPartition(
                    record.topic() + ".DLT",   // orders.DLT
                    record.partition()
                )
            );

        // Retry 3 times before sending to DLT
        FixedBackOff backOff = new FixedBackOff(1000L, 3);

        DefaultErrorHandler handler = new DefaultErrorHandler(recoverer, backOff);

        // Don't retry deserialization errors — they'll never succeed
        handler.addNotRetryableExceptions(SerializationException.class);

        return handler;
    }
}
```

### DLT consumer for investigation and replay
```java
@Component
public class OrdersDltConsumer {

    @KafkaListener(topics = "orders.DLT", groupId = "orders-dlt-monitor")
    public void handleDltMessage(
            @Payload byte[] rawPayload,
            @Header(KafkaHeaders.DLT_EXCEPTION_MESSAGE) String errorMsg,
            @Header(KafkaHeaders.DLT_ORIGINAL_OFFSET) long originalOffset,
            @Header(KafkaHeaders.DLT_ORIGINAL_TOPIC) String originalTopic) {

        log.error("DLT message from {}@{}: error={}",
            originalTopic, originalOffset, errorMsg);

        // Store raw bytes for forensic analysis
        dltRepository.save(DltRecord.builder()
            .rawPayload(rawPayload)
            .originalTopic(originalTopic)
            .originalOffset(originalOffset)
            .errorMessage(errorMsg)
            .arrivedAt(Instant.now())
            .build());

        // Alert if DLT accumulation rate exceeds threshold
        dltAlertService.recordFailure(originalTopic);
    }
}
```

### Root cause: schema mismatch
```java
// Prevention: use Schema Registry with BACKWARD compatibility
// Producer schema v2 must be backward-compatible with consumer schema v1

// In application.yml for consumers:
spring:
  kafka:
    consumer:
      value-deserializer: io.confluent.kafka.serializers.KafkaAvroDeserializer
      properties:
        schema.registry.url: http://schema-registry:8081
        specific.avro.reader: true
        # Never fail on unknown fields — forward compatibility
        # This is controlled by schema compatibility settings on the registry
```

### Schema evolution rules to prevent poison pills
- Always add new fields as **optional with defaults** — never add required fields
- BACKWARD compatible: new schema can read old messages
- FORWARD compatible: old schema can read new messages
- FULL compatible: both — the safest for multi-version deployments

