## Sync-to-Async Checkout Redesign

### Step 1: Classify operations by criticality
| Operation | Sync required? | Reason |
|---|---|---|
| Inventory reservation | YES | Must prevent oversell before confirming |
| Payment processing | YES | Must confirm charge before telling user success |
| Email confirmation | NO | Async: user can wait, retry on failure |
| Analytics logging | NO | Async: non-transactional, best-effort |

### Step 2: New synchronous critical path (~300ms)
```java
@PostMapping("/checkout")
@Transactional
public ResponseEntity<CheckoutResponse> checkout(@RequestBody CheckoutRequest req) {
    // 1. Reserve inventory (300ms) — synchronous, must succeed
    InventoryReservation reservation = inventoryService.reserve(req.getItems());

    // 2. Process payment (800ms → target: 300ms with direct API)
    PaymentResult payment = paymentService.charge(req.getPaymentMethod(), req.getTotal());

    // 3. Create order record + publish events atomically (Outbox pattern)
    Order order = Order.builder()
        .items(req.getItems())
        .reservation(reservation)
        .payment(payment)
        .status(OrderStatus.CONFIRMED)
        .build();
    orderRepository.save(order);

    // Outbox: persist events in same DB transaction
    outboxRepository.save(new OutboxEvent("order.confirmed", order.getId(),
        objectMapper.writeValueAsString(new OrderConfirmedEvent(order))));
    // Email and analytics events in outbox — picked up by relay

    return ResponseEntity.status(201).body(CheckoutResponse.of(order.getId()));
    // Response time: 300ms (inventory) + 300ms (payment) = ~600ms → further reduce
    // with payment pre-auth or async payment capture
}
```

### Step 3: Async email via Outbox relay
```java
@Component
public class OutboxRelay {
    @Scheduled(fixedDelay = 1000)
    @Transactional
    public void relay() {
        List<OutboxEvent> pending = outboxRepository.findPendingBatch(100);
        for (OutboxEvent event : pending) {
            kafkaTemplate.send(event.getTopic(), event.getAggregateId(), event.getPayload());
            event.markPublished();
        }
        outboxRepository.saveAll(pending);
    }
}

@KafkaListener(topics = "order.confirmed")
public void sendConfirmationEmail(OrderConfirmedEvent event) {
    // Runs async — outside the checkout transaction
    emailService.sendOrderConfirmation(event);
}
```

### Step 4: What if email sending fails?
```java
@KafkaListener(topics = "order.confirmed", containerFactory = "retryableFactory")
public void sendConfirmationEmail(OrderConfirmedEvent event) {
    try {
        emailService.sendOrderConfirmation(event);
    } catch (EmailException e) {
        // Kafka retry + DLT handles this — see RetryableTopic
        throw e; // re-throw to trigger retry
    }
}

// Spring Kafka @RetryableTopic
@RetryableTopic(
    attempts = "5",
    backoff = @Backoff(delay = 1000, multiplier = 2),
    dltStrategy = DltStrategy.FAIL_ON_ERROR
)
```

### Result
- Checkout response: ~600ms (inventory + payment only)
- With payment pre-auth or async capture: ~300ms
- Email and analytics: eventually consistent, guaranteed delivery via outbox

